{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Data types in numpy</h1>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.numpy.org/\">NumPy</a> provides powerful data structures for Python with multi-dimensional arrays and matrices. The execution speeed is faster than Python's native data structures. Take a look at a <a href=\"http://arogozhnikov.github.io/2015/01/06/benchmarks-of-speed-numpy-vs-all.html\">benchmarking result</a></p>\n<p>Refer the <a href=\"https://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/reference/\">documentation</a> for all the rich features and math functions.</p>\n<h3>Import</h3>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">numpy</code> is usually imported as alias <code class=\"language-text\">np</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> numpy <span class=\"token keyword\">as</span> np</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h3>Scalars</h3>\n<p>Numpy scalars provide signed and unsigned with different sizes. For example - <code class=\"language-text\">uint8</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">uint16</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">int8</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">int64</code> etc. Refer <a href=\"https://www.numpy.org/devdocs/user/basics.types.html\">NumPy Data types</a> for the complete list</p>\n<p>Initializing a scalar value <code class=\"language-text\">10</code> as,</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\">a <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> np<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>array<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Use <code class=\"language-text\">shape</code> attribute to verify the dimension of the array</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\">a<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>shape</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">()</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>We get <code class=\"language-text\">()</code> as the shape of array <code class=\"language-text\">a</code>. It means <strong>Zero dimension</strong> (or scalar). Basic operations can be performed against NumPy scalars</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>a <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">100</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\">b <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> a <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">15</span>\nb<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>shape</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">(25, ())</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>See the type of <code class=\"language-text\">b</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token builtin\">type</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>b<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">numpy.int64</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h3>Vectors</h3>\n<p>Create a vector [1, 2, 3, 4]</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\">v <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> np<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>array<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>v<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>shape<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">(4,)</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>The shape <code class=\"language-text\">(4,)</code> represents a <strong>1-dimensional</strong> array. We can access elements like using basic slicing and indexing operations</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'v[2] = {v[2]}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'v[1:] = {v[1:]}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'type(v[1:]) = {type(v[1:])}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'v[1:].shape = {v[1:].shape}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">v[2] = 3\nv[1:] = [2 3 4]\ntype(v[1:]) = &lt;class &#39;numpy.ndarray&#39;&gt;\nv[1:].shape = (3,)</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h3>Matrices</h3>\n<p>Create a <code class=\"language-text\">3 x 2</code> matrix</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\">m1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> np<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>array<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">12</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>m1<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'m1.shape = {m1.shape}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">[[ 1  2]\n [ 5  6]\n [10 12]]\nm1.shape = (3, 2)</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Access the elements</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-python line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'m1[2] = {m1[2]}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'m1[2][1] = {m1[2][1]}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'m1[1:] = \\n{m1[1:]}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token string\">'m1[:2] = \\n{m1[:2]}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">m1[2] = [10 12]\nm1[2][1] = 12\nm1[1:] = \n[[ 5  6]\n [10 12]]\nm1[:2] = \n[[1 2]\n [5 6]]</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"a","description":"a"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/math/"}}